The '''Lord of the Iron Islands''' is the ruler of the stronghold of [[Pyke (castle)|Pyke]], the capital of the [[Iron Islands]]. The holder is the ruler over all of the islands.  

Before the [[War of Conquest|Targaryen Conquest]], the Iron Islands were originally a sovereign nation. The [[ironborn]] also controlled [[The Riverlands|the Riverlands]], which they had conquered in turn from [[The Stormlands|the Stormlands]]. The title was first created after the ironborn became vassals of [[House Targaryen]]. [[House Greyjoy]] have been the Lords of the Iron Islands for hundreds of years.

===[[Season 2]]===
After naming himself King of the Iron Islands, [[Balon Greyjoy|King Balon Greyjoy]] invaded [[The North|the North]] by sending his daughter [[Yara Greyjoy|Yara]] to seize [[Deepwood Motte]], his brother [[Victarion Greyjoy|Victarion]] to seize [[Moat Cailin]] and his only living son [[Theon Greyjoy|Theon]] to raide the [[Stony Shore]].&lt;ref&gt;[[The Ghost of Harrenhal]]&lt;/ref&gt; Despite Theon being King Balon's only son, Balon has named his daughter Yara as his heir.&lt;ref&gt;[[What is Dead May Never Die]]&lt;/ref&gt;
